The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Wednesday, December 29, 2004 

 Coral reefs lost forever

 US seismologist Charles F. Richter who invented, with his colleague Beno Gutenberg, the scale to measure seismographic activity. (AFP)

 Bangkok, Dec. 28 (Reuters): The tsunami which killed hundreds of people in southern Thailand may also have killed the coral reefs which attract large numbers of foreign tourists, a Thai marine scientist was quoted today as saying.

 ?The impact is irreversible,? the English-language Nation newspaper quoted Thon Thamrongnawasawasdi of Bangkok?s Kasetsart University as saying. ?We will never get back the past richness.? 




